\pard\plain \s41\li360\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid Performs Lagrange interpolation on a Galois field GF(2^d), where d is the degree of primitive_poly.\par
\par
Given the data of n (x,y) points on a Galois field GF=GF(2^d), returns the outputs of a polynomial \par
of degree n-1 that passes through all of these points, evaluated at the list of points at_points.\par
Notice that GF is not unique, and must be determined by a primitive polynomial of degree d on GF(2),\par
which must be specified in the inputs.\par
